                        <h2 class="mb-3 blogTitle h-auto">How does a good web design prove to be an asset to a business?</h2>
                        <p>A website is one of the most important assets for a business. As your audience are majorly spending their time online, chance are high they will know you online itself. A website is a prime thing that a person gazes at before making any buying decision.</p>
                        <p>It does not just make your audience aware of what your business sells but most importantly, it makes them aware of your existence in the market.</p>
                        <p>Website plays a very crucial role in the lead generation as well as conversions for any business. So, let’s discuss the importance of <a href="why-website-design-and-development-is-one-of-the-most-important-aspects-in-business">creative website design</a> below:</p>
                        <h3 class="mb-3 mt-4">1. Makes your brand’s image stronger</h3>
                        <p>Your website is indeed the reflection of your brand and that is why people trust it more than any other thing about your business. A good website has a greater chance of boosting conversions for your business. Your website must reflect everything and anything about your business so that your audience can have in-depth knowledge about you.</p>
                        <img src="../images/blogs/Website-brand’s-image.jpg" alt="A good website design has a greater chance of boosting conversions for your business" class="img-fluid my-4">
                        <p>Having a well-developed quirky website with good color usage, fonts, visuals, information, and other elements will not just boost the brand’s image but also build people’s trust in your business. Furthermore, a consistent website in which you as a brand have frequent postings about any latest announcements would highly build your audience’s trust in your business which leads to increased sales. So, develop your <a href="how-to-create-your-business-as-a-brand-why-branding-is-important">brand’s</a> website accordingly.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="mb-3 pt-2">2. Boosts customer service and satisfaction</h3>
                        <p>When your audience visits your website, they get an insight into how you treat your customers and what are the positives they can get from your brand. This makes them aware of whether your business would be helpful to them or not. So, <strong>investing in a good website design is of utmost importance</strong>. This will make your audience believe that you would provide them the value for their money.</p>
                        <p>That is why hiring a good <a href="./website-design-and-development-company">website designer</a> who knows the latest trends in the market is a must. Invest in an up-to-date custom web design with all the latest technology and navigation which makes your business appear open and welcoming. Do not forget to provide your audience with a pleasant experience each time they visit your website. This way, your customer’s satisfaction with the brand will enhance.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="my-4">
                        <h3 class="mb-3 pt-2">3. Help your brand get an edge over your competitors</h3>
                        <p>If you are willing to outshine your competition in the market and become a leader in your business, then <strong>you need to have a good website design first</strong>. A design that has an edge to beat your competitors in the market. For instance, if your competitors have a good <strong>website design</strong> and are preferred by millions of people; how would you survive in such a market? Well, it is not impossible but to beat your competition, it is highly crucial to come up with an interesting <strong>website design</strong>.</p>
                        <img src="../images/blogs/Website-Design-Layout.jpg" alt="powerful website design that will help you improve your brand’s" class="img-fluid my-4">
                        <p>Improve your website’s layout and overall functionality which distinguishes you from your competitor’s website. Your main objective should be about how you can become better in your market. If you conduct strong research, you will be able to come up with a <strong>powerful website design that will help you improve your brand’s</strong> functions and help you edge over your competitors. So, this justifies your query of <strong>what is the website design</strong>.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="mb-3 pt-2">4. Helps to improve the leads and overall conversions of your business</h3>
                        <p>Coming up with a decent <strong>website design</strong> would help you take control of your business over and above your competitors. The <a href="what-makes-a-good-website-design-and-why-it-matters">best website design</a> would help your audience’s eyes to drive where they exactly intend to go on your website. And this is an example of improved <strong>website design</strong>. You can use a good navigation bar to redirect all your traffic to the section where you have all the offers, promotions, and <a href="knowledge-base">call-to-action buttons</a>. This will lead to conversions.</p>
                        <p>Furthermore, if you develop clickable facets within your website, it would be a lot easier for your audience to scroll through your website and hence this enhances the user experience for both the new and the existing customers. Not just this, <strong>developing a mobile-friendly website</strong> is a sure-shot way to improve and <strong>boost the conversion rates of your website</strong>. Always keep in mind that <strong>smartphones have a greater conversion than websites</strong>. So, <strong>mobile-friendly websites</strong> are the demand of the hour.</p> 
                    </div>
                    <div class="my-4">
                        <h3 class="mb-3 pt-2">5. No bounce rates</h3>
                        <p>Well, if your website has a good layout, then it would not have minimal or no bounce rates at all. A <strong>website visitor</strong> sticks to the website only when they have a genuine reason for it, that is, a well-developed and good-looking, and useful website. Websites with bad layouts and <strong>web designs</strong> are likely to have more bounce rates than usual and this way their business can never grow.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="pt-2">
                        <img src="../images/blogs/Website-loading-speed.jpg" alt="develop a website with a quick loading speed" class="img-fluid mb-3">
                        <p>To have no bounce rates at all, it is better to <strong>develop a website with a quick loading speed</strong>. Yes, loading speed matters the most to reduce the bounce rates on your website. No user or website visitor has enough time to remain on your website while it’s loading. Several websites are offering the same to them so why would they prefer yours with a slow loading speed? That is why work on the loading speed more than any other thing so that it does not just keep your audience engaged but also makes them have an in-depth visit to your website. A good loading speed will influence the sales to funnel too.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="my-4">
                        <h3 class="mb-2">6. Enhance your SEO tactics</h3>
                         <a href="./digital-marketing-agency">Search Engine Optimization (SEO)</a> is also one big factor for the success <strong>of your business online</strong>. Different components used on a web page will have a significant impact on your website. These components will make the <strong>search engines</strong> crawl and rank your page on the <strong>SERPs</strong>. 
                         <img src="../images/blogs/Enhance-your-SEO-tactics.jpg" alt="SEO-friendly responsive web designing" class="img-fluid my-4">
                         <p>Additionally, some businesses prioritize design over functionality. This is something that can ultimately harm your <a href="6-genuine-digital-marketing-tips-for-business-growth">SEO strategy</a>. That is the reason why you must use <strong>SEO-friendly responsive web designing</strong> elements and techniques to enhance the visibility of your website. </p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                         <h2 class="mb-4 pt-3">Top 4 elements to be used to generate a high converting website design</h2>
                         <img src="../images/blogs/Website-Design-Elements.jpg" alt="Top 4 Website Design Elements to be used to generate a High Converting Website Design" class="img-fluid mb-3">
                         <p>If you have been underestimating the power of the colors, fonts, and typography as well as the necessity of a <strong>responsive website design</strong>, then you might have to change your perspective. Why? Because what you have in your head is something outdated and to come up with a trendy touch; you will have to use <a href="./why-website-design-and-development-is-one-of-the-most-important-aspects-in-business">modern website designing techniques</a> to enhance the visibility of your website. </p>
                            <p>Here are a few elements to be used with your <strong>website design and development:</strong></p>
                            <div class="mb-4">
                              <h3 class="mb-3">Include visual content on your website</h3>
                              <p>Well, with visual content, we mean, a mix of GIFs, stock or real-time images, films, infographics, etc. These elements have greater accessibility to grab the visitor’s attention so why not use it to enhance the conversion rate of your website? </p>
                              <p>Moreover, you cannot use these visual elements as and when you want them on your website. You need to have a proper hierarchy of visual content planned and implemented. </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="mb-4">
                              <h3 class="mb-3">Cogent Call To Actions</h3>
                               <p>What is the main aim of your website? It is to serve your audience and compel them to complete their purchase from your brand or avail of your services, right? So, for that, you need to have compelling <a href="./knowledge-base">CTAs</a> placed on your website that not just persuade your visitors but also make them stay and sit on your website a little longer. Catchy <a href="./knowledge-base">Call To Action Buttons</a> must be placed at different sites on the website so that it helps your audience notice and respond to them with sales.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="mb-4">
                              <h3 class="mb-3">Understandable fonts and typography</h3>
                              <p>Well, not every font is a good fit for a website. You just cannot use a random font and use it for your website. There are a huge number of fonts that can be used differently for every niche of business. The general rule while selecting a font is that it must be easy to read so that each of your website viewers can know what message you want to convey to them. Fonts must be visible and not many fancy fonts are good for any business.</p>
                              <p>There are different fonts described for different websites. For an instance, if your website is to serve a younger audience, then it can be a stylish and fun font. This is because the young audience prefers quirkiness. However, if your website is specified for an old or aged audience, then it must be clean, bold, and simple to understand fonts. This audience prefers easy-to-read fonts.</p>
                              <p>A font, in general, reflects your brand’s personality and makes your brand look professional, fun, and youthful. </p>
                            </div>
                        
                            <div class="mb-4">
                              <h3 class="mb-3">Make your website accessible to all</h3>
                              <p>Your website must be designed in a manner that is accessible to all. By accessible we mean ALL, people with disabilities too. Well, a <strong>good and well-developed website would make the browsing experience better.</strong></p>
                              <p>While designing your website, make sure that you are keeping every audience in mind, the disabled ones too. Many <a href="https://asesasoft.com">website design company</a> are not even aware of how they can make their websites accessible to the disabled audience. This can be so challenging but it is not impossible. You can use solutions available on the web to simplify this process.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="mb-4">
                              <h2 class="mb-2">Final Words</h2>
                              <p>In this modern era, many businesses have already created websites that are accessible to their customers and at the same time are responsive. With the help of a <a href="how-custom-web-design-benefits-your-business">custom web design</a>, business owners are creating a welcoming online environment for their audience and hence this will not just thrive your business to the next level but also make it profitable.</p>
